the
financial
results
of
computer
firms
has
been
a
tough
job
lately
.

Take
Microsoft
Corp.
,
the
largest
maker
of
personal
computer
software
and
generally
considered
an
industry
bellwether
.

In
July
,
the
company
stunned
Wall
Street
with
the
prediction
that
growth
in
the
personal
computer
business
overall
would
be
only
00
%
in
0000
,
a
modest
increase
when
compared
with
the
sizzling
expansion
of
years
past
.

Investors
--
taking
this
as
a
sign
that
a
broad
industry
slump
was
in
the
offing
--
reacted
by
selling
the
company
's
stock
,
which
lost
$
0.00
that
day
to
close
at
$
00
in
national
over-the-counter
trading
.

But
that
was
all
of
three
months
ago
.

Last
week
,
Microsoft
said
it
expects
revenue
for
its
first
quarter
ended
Sept.
00
to
increase
00
%
.

The
announcement
caused
the
company
's
stock
to
surge
$
0.00
to
close
at
$
00.00
a
share
.

Microsoft
's
surprising
strength
is
one
example
of
the
difficulty
facing
investors
looking
for
