in
history
have
been
reasonably
comfortable
.

The
0000
crash
was
``
a
false
alarm
however
you
view
it
,
''
says
University
of
Chicago
economist
Victor
<_UNK>
.

The
market
seems
increasingly
disconnected
from
the
rest
of
the
nation
.

Its
spasms
ca
n't
be
traced
to
fundamental
business
conditions
,
nor
do
