.

The
Fed
,
which
until
Friday
had
been
resisting
moves
to
ease
credit
,
is
now
poised
to
pour
money
into
the
economy
if
needed
to
soothe
the
markets
.

Fed
officials
may
protest
that
this
does
n't
necessarily
mean
a
fundamental
change
in
their
interest-rate
